This paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for spam filtering, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for spam filtering, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of homomorphic encryption and randomization also suggests a potential connection to cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses dimensionality reduction techniques, which can be categorized under databases (cs.DB).
